23]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>如果我从今天的蓝牙扬声器中了解到一件事，那就是对于普通消费者来说，选择非常好。然而，这并没有使筛选数十种选择以找到最佳购买的过程变得更容易。所以我开始测试一些不同价位的最受欢迎的型号，从入门级到中端到昂贵。我试过的大多数扬声器在第一次听时听起来都不错；只有通过并排比较，我才开始弄清楚其中的细微差别。仅阅读规格表就到此为止了。因此，我们更多地关注音频质量和动态范围，同时也考虑其他因素，如效用和价格。最终，没有最好的便携式蓝牙扬声器，但我们发现了很多适合各种用例和价位的好选择。</p><h2><strong>考虑什么</strong></h2><h3>防风雨</h3><p><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.iec.ch/ip-ratings">IP 等级</a>（入口保护）是您经常在产品规格表中看到的字母数字指示符，用于定义产品对固体物体（污垢、灰尘、手指？）和水的测试抵抗力。它通常是两个数字的组合，第一个表示固体物体进入，第二个表示水。前者从 0（无保护）到 6（防尘）。防水等级从 0（无保护）到 9（防止浸泡和高压喷射）。当使用 X 代替数字时，这意味着该产品未经过电阻测试。如果它是防水的，它可能对固体有一些先天的抵抗力，但这并不能保证。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> IP67 是当今常见的评级，表明扬声器具有高抗性和潜在的坚固性。这些对于在游泳池或浴缸中快速扣篮是安全的，并且在雨中或淋浴时应该更合适。它们也是海滩、游乐场和其他恶劣环境的不错选择。</p><p>此外，带有端口<em>和</em>高额定值的扬声器通常会在充电端口或辅助端口上安装一个紧密贴合的盖子。如果您计划使用这些端口，那可能会限制产品抵御这些因素的额定能力。</p><p>在做出决定时，请考虑 IP 等级以及您打算如何使用蓝牙扬声器。例如，如果您主要在室内使用它，那么花钱买一个 IP 等级较低、声音更好的模型可能是值得的。</p><h3>电池寿命</h3><p>本指南的重点是便携式蓝牙扬声器，虽然“便携式”可能是一个相对术语，但这些设备通常适用于可能发现自己远离电源插座的人。如今，大约 12 小时的运行时间似乎是基准，但显然，扬声器的电池寿命越长越好。</p><p>也就是说，在查看电池规格时要小心，因为它们经常列出最长运行时间（“最多”x 小时数）。这通常意味着他们以中低音量进行测试。如果您喜欢响亮的音乐，通常最终会将预期的使用时间减少一半或更多。幸运的是，一些制造商还列出了以最大音量使用时的预期电池寿命小时数，这种透明性值得赞赏。</p><p>此外，如果您的蓝牙扬声器也恰好具有 WiFi 连接，则它们通常设计为具有始终在线的功能。与短时间不使用后进入睡眠状态的普通蓝牙扬声器不同，这些扬声器通常会保持清醒状态（以听取您的命令）并慢慢耗尽电池电量。如果您出门在外，请记住在不使用时手动关闭这些扬声器，以最大限度地延长电池寿命。</p><h3>范围</h3><p>蓝牙范围是一项棘手的业务。一些公司列出了他们产品的最长可能范围，通常是在户外和无障碍视线测试环境中。其他公司在规格表上坚持 30 英尺的范围并保持不变，即使他们可能正在运行蓝牙 4.x 或 5.x。这可能低估了扬声器的潜力，但不可预测的环境会影响范围，并且承诺月球只是为了得到抱怨是没有意义的。</p><p>我在蹲下时遇到过信号掉落问题，手机放在牛仔裤的前袋里，距离公寓内的扬声器仅 30 英尺。无论列出的蓝牙连接范围如何，我都在多个设备上遇到了这个问题。</p><p>如果您要举办露台派对并躲在里面，最好将源设备放在附近以防万一。很难衡量任何环境的哪些方面可能会干扰蓝牙信号。一般来说，将 100 英尺左右或以上的范围规格视为完美世界场景。</p><h3>潜伏</h3><p>对于那些将扬声器用于计算机输出或作为显示器和流媒体盒等设置的迷你条形音箱解决方案的人来说，这是一个次要的提及。发现您的扬声器的延迟不够低，无法避免唇形同步问题，这很烦人。幸运的是，如今<em>大多数</em>扬声器似乎并不经常遇到这些问题。在我试过的几十个扬声器中，只有少数几个有持续的、明显的口型同步问题。除了偶尔出现的故障外，我们所有的选择在这方面都运作良好。</p><p>如果您计划经常使用扬声器播放视频，请寻找具有最新蓝牙版本（4.x 或 5.x）和低延迟编解码器（如 aptX）的设备。还要确保扬声器靠近源设备，因为距离可能是一个因素。不过，要完全避免这个问题，请考虑使用有线辅助输入。</p><h2><strong>价格：50 至 200 美元</strong></h2><h3>Tribit StormBox Micro 2（60 美元）</h3><p><core-commerce id="59342dcbd97b433eb4b0cea2601d2269" data-type="product-list"></p><p><strong>蓝牙：</strong> 5.3<br><strong>电池寿命：</strong>长达 12 小时<br><strong>防护等级：</strong> IP67<br><strong>辅助输入：</strong>不适用<br><strong>频率范围：</strong> 70Hz - 20kHz<br><strong>应用程序：</strong>没有</p><p>If you&#39;re just looking for a small speaker that can kick out some decent volume, the <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfuFzh0yGiZ9XlC2zXyydFGwoNIdOpGopFvwCXvWnSvl&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FTribit-StormBox-Portable-Speaker-Built%2Fdp%2FB09Q59321N%2F">Tribit StormBox Micro 2</a> fits the bill. The audio quality here is fine; it doesn&#39;t stand out in terms of fidelity, but the volume you get from this affordable little speaker is what makes it a good choice. If you&#39;re bopping about outdoors on your bike or chilling in the park, it&#39;s usually more about portability and volume anyway. The rubbery rear strap works well on relatively thin things like belts, backpacks and bike handlebars.</p><p> While it&#39;s small and affordable, the speaker doubles as a USB-C powerbank to charge your devices in a pinch and you can wirelessly connect two of them for party mode or stereo sound. It also supports voice assistants for both iOS and Android users.</p><h3> UE Wonderboom 3 ($100)</h3><p><core-commerce id="9eba7be9a300458cbc5a9ef08d53a35b" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <strong>Bluetooth:</strong> N/A<br> <strong>Battery life:</strong> Up to 14 hours<br> <strong>IP Rating:</strong> IP67<br> <strong>Aux inputs:</strong> N/A<br> <strong>Frequency range:</strong> 75Hz - 20kHz<br> <strong>App:</strong> No</p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwOUtYMjdLR04_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZngtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjFiZDNhMGJkLTdjYTEtNDU0Yi1iNGNkLTNhZmE1NWQ1MTg1MCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAcSXh9IntFBz9E_YRmFYXafKbNCdsCUciTZRWM1oFQPK&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09KX27KGN">UE Wonderboom 3</a> is a tiny yet powerful portable, delivering the biggest sound in its size range that we tested. It&#39;s still a cute, barrel-shaped small speaker with a nubby little strap that probably needs a carabiner to help attach it to most things. But this refreshed model includes a couple of bright new colors, an extra hour of battery life and improved wireless range. With an IP67 rating on top of the company&#39;s five-foot drop test durability, it can go with you almost anywhere and survive to tell the tale.</p><p> The audio quality is punchy and bright enough for what you&#39;d expect at this scale and price range. Although there&#39;s no app support or connectivity with the rest of the Ultimate Ears speaker lineup, you can easily pair it with a second Wonderboom for stereo sound. There&#39;s also an outdoor mode button on the bottom that boosts the mid and high range to help the audio carry over a greater distance.</p><h3> Soundcore Motion+ ($107)</h3><p><core-commerce id="2e6fb4f492d94edeb7053651d4479f22" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <strong>Bluetooth:</strong> 5.0<br> <strong>Battery life:</strong> Up to 12 hours<br> <strong>IP Rating:</strong> IPX7<br> <strong>Aux inputs:</strong> 3.5mm<br> <strong>Frequency range:</strong> 50Hz - 40kHz<br> <strong>App:</strong> Yes</p><p> This nondescript wedge of a wireless <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Bbmtlci1Tb3VuZGNvcmUtQmx1ZXRvb3RoLUN1c3RvbWl6YWJsZS1XYXRlcnByb29mL2RwL0IwN1AzOU1MS0g_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZngtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjFiZDNhMGJkLTdjYTEtNDU0Yi1iNGNkLTNhZmE1NWQ1MTg1MCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAb-0WsULqYGKiDsej66iyhZ6CEPaodgeQvSYLBftNnhm&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAnker-Soundcore-Bluetooth-Customizable-Waterproof%2Fdp%2FB07P39MLKH">speaker</a> could easily slip under your radar, but it&#39;s worth a listen. It has a bright and bassy output, which is helped along by Qualcomm aptX support for hi-res audio. This Anker Soundcore device has a solid, slightly heavy build with a metal front speaker grille, a soft-touch rubberized exterior (that loves your greasy fingerprints) and IPX7 water resistance. While it&#39;s not the lightest or most portable, it has good sound, especially for the price. Plus the app offers EQ customization, so you can fine tune to your liking.</p><p> There&#39;s also a 3.5mm aux input for wired connections. That&#39;s fortuitous, as we found that this small speaker works well as a mini soundbar alternative and the wired input offers a foolproof connection.</p><h3> Soundcore Trance Go ($120)</h3><p><core-commerce id="ac8cd705aeaa496e8d0f121ca59cbcb4" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <strong>Bluetooth:</strong> 5.0<br> <strong>Battery life:</strong> Up to 24 hours<br> <strong>IP Rating:</strong> IPX7<br> <strong>Aux inputs:</strong> 3.5mm<br> <strong>Frequency range:</strong> 55Hz - 20kHz<br> <strong>App:</strong> Yes</p><p> If you have a large indoor space, backyard or similar and want something with powerful long-throw sound in an affordable package, the Anker <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAa5TY3n0yrEcRNZLmJbHPS6kCeoANiIUHxiGc-JumY-1&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSoundcore-Bluetooth-Playtime-Technology-Waterproof%2Fdp%2FB085C9ZGSG">Soundcore Trance Go</a> may surprise you. This barebones speaker is bigger than most others in this price range and would weigh down a backpack a bit at about six pounds, but offers a carry strap, up to 24 hours runtime, a port for charging your devices and an aux input.</p><p> If you&#39;re close by, you&#39;ll hear the thump of its low-end and some decent highs. It&#39;s generally tuned for covering big spaces, though, and its sound won&#39;t work for every situation. This performs like a mini loudspeaker, putting out up to around 98dB, albeit with a slightly thinner sound that won&#39;t overpower the environment. You can also use Soundcore&#39;s app to apply EQ presets or customize as you see fit. If you have two of these, they can pair for stereo sound, or connect 100 or more Trance Go speakers via the app&#39;s PartyCast feature.</p><h3> JBL Flip 6 ($130)</h3><p><core-commerce id="14990fc7abe94758b0870f3ba81461fc" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <strong>Bluetooth:</strong> 5.1<br> <strong>Battery life:</strong> Up to 12 hours<br> <strong>IP Rating:</strong> IP67<br> <strong>Aux inputs:</strong> N/A<br> <strong>Frequency range:</strong> 63Hz - 20kHz<br> <strong>App:</strong> Yes</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSW